        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "how to find the node which has child node while parsing XML file using DOM parser in java",
        "body": "<p>I want to parse a xml document and convert into json. \nI'm facing problem in finding which node has child and which has not.<\/p>\n\n<p><em>Example :<\/em> <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;Bank&gt;\n    &lt;Account&gt;\n        &lt;Id&gt;1001&lt;/Id&gt;\n        &lt;Name&gt;Jack Robinson&lt;/Name&gt;\n       &lt;Amt&gt;10000&lt;/Amt&gt;\n    &lt;/Account&gt;\n&lt;/Bank&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>In this xml file, I want to find first Bank node has a child element i.e. Account , same like Account node has child node i.e. Id,Name,Amt.\nBut Id, Name and Amt node does not have any childs, so I want to find like this which node has child child and which node has not?<\/p>\n\n<p>I'm trying with <strong>node.hasChildNodes()<\/strong> method but it will return true for each node.<\/p>\n\n<p>Please help me to solve this problem...<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 37586101,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "xml",
            "xml-parsing",
            "domparser"
        ],
        "score": 1,
        "accepted_answer_id": 37586702,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 3336
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/998d26fea784db33e0fb7fb5131f3760?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 8559041,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 6413610,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6413610/kalam",
                "reputation": 46,
                "display_name": "Kalam"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1464856705,
            "creation_date": 1464856705,
            "body": "<p><strong>node.hasChildNodes()<\/strong> returns true because it finds the empty text element as a child.<br>\nSo in your case <strong>Bank<\/strong> has child <strong>empty text<\/strong> and then <strong>Account<\/strong>.<br>\nA solution is to remove the formatting elements from the XML, and then parse it.\nYou can check if a node is an <strong>empty text<\/strong> or an element node by using <strong>node.getNodeType() == Node.ELEMENT_NODE<\/strong>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 37586702,
            "question_id": 37586101
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/eYlBN.jpg?s=256",
